    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-15T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="72"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">859.85/703: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-15T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 15, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>139. Your 278, July 26. All immobilized Danish vessels in American and Philippine
                    Island ports have been requisitioned.</p>
                <p>The act authorizing such acquisition of foreign merchant vessels provides that
                    just compensation shall be determined and made to the owners.</p>
                <p>There is no question that this Government’s right to do this exists under
                    international law.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
